      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, based on the text you provided, that clause allows the supplier to increase rates unexpectedly, specifically during June through August. The phrase \"effective immediately upon the start of said month\" means there is no advance notice or waiting period to prevent them from applying the 5% surcharge the moment the season begins. You should strongly advise the boss that this section is risky because it permits sudden price changes without prior warning.",
